1. Which of the following is true?

> RDD Actions return non-RDDs
- Spark Datasets are currently compatible with Python
- SparkContext is considered to be the entry-point for working with Spark dataframes
- RDD stands for Resilient Dynamic Dataset

2. Which of the following are ways to display or data from a Spark dataframe?

> SparkDF.show()
> SparkDF.first()
> SparkDF.head(n)
> SparkDF.take(n)

3. True or False: “toDF()” is a method to create a new Spark dataframe comprised by selected columns of a pre-existing one

> True

4. Which of the following is a method to create an instance of a given dataframe TheDF with a new column called Weight_Unadjusted, initialized as a copy of a pre-existing column called Weight?

- TheDF.withColumn(“Weight_Unadjusted”, “Weight”)
> TheDF.withColumn(“Weight_Unadjusted”, col(“Weight”))
- TheDF.withColumn(col(“Weight_Unadjusted”), “Weight”)

5. Which of the following is not usable to describe a dataframe?

- df.columns
- df.dtypes
- df.count()
> df.rows()

6. Which of the following functions/methods creates a row for each value in a given list (or array, or similar structure)?

- toDF()
> explode()
- groupBy()
- filter()

7. When working with a Spark dataframe, to make a new column that is assigned to one value/expression if a condition is fulfilled, and another value/expression if the condition is unfulfilled, what sequence of methods would be used?

- when().else()
- if().else()
- if().elif().else()
> when().otherwise()
